Phase 3 — The critical business rule tests
EMPLOYEE updates their own task:
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/1
Auth: emp1 / emp123

{
    "status": "IN_PROGRESS"
}
Expected: 200 OK
--------------------------------------------
EMPLOYEE updates someone else's task 
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/2
Auth: emp1 / emp123

{
    "status": "DONE"
}
Expected: error from service layer
--------------------------------------------
deleting project with incomplete tasks — must fail:
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/projects/1
Auth: admin / admin123
Expected: error — incomplete tasks exist
--------------------------------------------
Mark all tasks as DONE:
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/1
Auth: admin / admin123
{ "status": "DONE" }
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/tasks/2
Auth: admin / admin123
{ "status": "DONE" }
--------------------------------------------
Now delete project 
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/projects/1
Auth: admin / admin123
Expected: 204 No Content
--------------------------------------------
Verify cascade — tasks must be gone too:
GET http://localhost:8080/api/tasks
Auth: admin / admin123
Expected: empty list — cascade delete worked
